snippet: Ayer tuvimos que llevar de nuevo a nuestro bebé de urgencia, ya que tenía conjuntivitis cuando fuimos a por ella al cole. Nos atendió el mismo pediatra que la vez anterior, un pediatra llamado Roberto. Muy majo y atento. Examinó a nuestra hija, nos dijo qué tenía y nos mandó un colirio con antibiótico. Hoy por la mañana ya está mucho mejor. Gran equipo el del hospital!

extracted_snippet.translated: I go to the emergency room with my husband who has been complaining for weeks of punctures and pressure in the lower right part of the abdomen and we wait 5 hours and in the end he tells us that he may have a hernia. We ask him to do an echo and he tells us that he doesn't know. He can and that he is going to ask for an ultrasound first. Then the doctor comes out with a piece of paper and says that he has to make the appointment at his health center. Wasn't that what the doctor was asking for? Having the ultrasound machine right at his side. What a shame!

snippet:
Urgencias pediátricas: dos veces que hemos acudido con nuestro bebé de ahora dos años y las dos veces diagnóstico equivocado. La primera vez, el bebé con 40 de fiebre, medio desmayado. Como no fueron capaces de verle nada, dijeron que era otitis....Ya para decir algo. Al día siguiente en otro centro, diagnosticaron escarlatina. La segunda vez, hace una semana, acudimos con la boca del bebé llena de puntitos rojos, fiebre y falta de apetito. Le comento al medico que igual es boca manos pies. Nos mandan una prueba de estreptococos. Una hora esperando. Negativo. El diagnóstico del pediatra: "catarro"... Le pregunto al medico cómo sabe que no es boca manos pies con los síntomas tan claros y me dice que no lo parece... Al día siguiente, en nuestro centro de salud del barrio: diagnóstico: BOCA MANOS PIES y bronquitis!!!
Me parece que son peligrosos los pediatras de este centro. No sé si es porque les falta la experiencia o porque son malos profesionales. Lo único bueno es que  tardan poco para atenderte y las enfermeras son muy amables. Pero, por favor, no lleven a sus bebés allí!

extracted_snippet.translated:
Pediatric emergencies: twice we have gone with our now two-year-old baby and both times we got the wrong diagnosis. The first time, the baby had a fever of 40, half fainted. Since they were not able to see anything, they said it was otitis... That's enough to say something. The next day at another center, they diagnosed scarlet fever. The second time, a week ago, we came with the baby's mouth full of red spots, fever and lack of appetite. I told the doctor that it might be mouth, hands, feet. They send us a strep test. An hour waiting. Negative. The pediatrician's diagnosis: "cold"... I ask the doctor how he knows it's not mouth, hands, feet with the symptoms so clear and he tells me that it doesn't seem like it... The next day, at our neighborhood health center: diagnosis: MOUTH HANDS FEET and bronchitis!!!
It seems to me that the pediatricians at this center are dangerous. I don't know if it's because they lack experience or because they are bad professionals. The only good thing is that they take little time to see you and the nurses are very friendly. But please don't take your babies there!
